ğŸ§ ICharacter (interface)
class ICharacter {
public:
    virtual std::string const & getName() const = 0;
    virtual void equip(AMateria* m) = 0;
    virtual void unequip(int idx) = 0;
    virtual void use(int idx, ICharacter& target) = 0;
};


ğŸ‘¤ Character (implÃ©mentation)
Nom, inventaire (4 AMateria*)

equip() : ajoute au 1er slot libre

unequip(idx) : met Ã  nullptr (ne delete pas)

use(idx, target) : appelle materia->use(target)

Copie profonde (constructeur/affectation)

Destructeur : libÃ¨re toutes les Materias



ğŸ§ª IMateriaSource / MateriaSource
class IMateriaSource {
public:
    virtual void learnMateria(AMateria*) = 0;
    virtual AMateria* createMateria(std::string const & type) = 0;
};


learnMateria() : stocke jusqu'Ã  4 modÃ¨les

createMateria(type) : retourne un clone du modÃ¨le correspondant


ğŸ§ª Exemple de test
IMateriaSource* src = new MateriaSource();
src->learnMateria(new Ice());
src->learnMateria(new Cure());

ICharacter* me = new Character("me");
AMateria* tmp;

tmp = src->createMateria("ice");
me->equip(tmp);
tmp = src->createMateria("cure");
me->equip(tmp);

ICharacter* bob = new Character("bob");
me->use(0, *bob);
me->use(1, *bob);

delete bob;
delete me;
delete src;

âœ… RÃ©sultat attendu
* shoots an ice bolt at bob *
* heals bob's wounds *


